    "This is defined as an MLP that considers the updated feature vectors of nodes (h T v) on the whole graph (v ∈ G) to produce a prediction and is defined as:ŷ = R({h T v |v ∈ G})(3)In order to make the GCN architecture scale to large graphs, the GraphSAGE [99] architecture changes the message function.",
    "Rather than taking messages from the entire neighbourhood of a node, a random sample is used.",
    "This reduces the number of messages that require processing, resulting in an architecture that works well on large graphs.",
